Package: ZIMLN
Type: Package
Title: Zero-Inflated Multivariate Rounded Log-Normal Model for Microbiome Count Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Shuangjie", "Zhang", email = "szhan209@tamu.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A Bayesian zero-inflated multivariate rounded log-normal (ZI-MLN)
    model for next-generation sequencing microbiome abundance data. The model
    infers the interaction (covariance) structure between microbial features
    directly from observed counts in the presence of covariates and excess
    zeros, using a Dirichlet-Laplace joint-sparsity prior on a low-rank plus
    diagonal covariance decomposition and a probit zero-inflation component.
    Methods are described in Zhang, Shuler, Lee and Jeganathan (2023)
    <doi:10.1214/22-AOAS1690>.
